Mobiles.Name: herring
Mobiles.Long_Description: A herring is swimming towards you in an aggressive manner.
Mobiles.Description: A herring has unusually long teeth for such a little creature.

Mobiles.Name: lemminkainen
Mobiles.Long_Description: Lemminkainen is here. He offers you a beer.
Mobiles.Description:
Lemminkainen sings a happy song about drinking beer and seducing all the 
ladies in sight. He is a fat guy with a serious weight problem.

Mobiles.Name: tuuslar wizard
Mobiles.Long_Description: Tuuslar the wind-wizard is here, doing his dirty deeds.
Mobiles.Description:
Tuuslar the wind-wizard scratches his belly and considers you for his next 
meal.

- I lay like dead,
  a dizzy slave of sleep,
  frozen like a lifeless clot,
  numbed upon the hilltop. -

Mobiles.Name: wife fat
Mobiles.Long_Description: Tuuslar's fat wife is here, trying to seduce you.
Mobiles.Description: Tuuslar's fat wife licks her lips and winks suggestively at you.

Mobiles.Name: saam
Mobiles.Long_Description: A Saam is here, singing a song with no words.
Mobiles.Description: A Saam says: "Have you seen my rain-deer?"

Mobiles.Name: shaman saam old
Mobiles.Long_Description: An Old Saam shaman has summoned all four winds here.
Mobiles.Description: An Old Saam shaman looks like he needs a bath. Ack.

Mobiles.Name: poro
Mobiles.Long_Description: A poro lowers his hornie head and attacks you.
Mobiles.Description:
A poro has razor-sharp horns on his head, which is quite unusual for 
little animal such as a poro...

Mobiles.Name: sorts
Mobiles.Long_Description: A sorts attacks you, screaming annoyingly.
Mobiles.Description: A sorts seems to be a very violent creature.

Mobiles.Name: warlord viking
Mobiles.Long_Description: The Viking Warlord is here, yelling at he's men.
Mobiles.Description: The Viking Warlord says "So are you willing to join us on our next massacre?"

Mobiles.Name: warrior viking
Mobiles.Long_Description: A Viking warrior is here, singing he's battlesong.
Mobiles.Description:
A Viking warrior looks too tired to fight you. He's battlesong is 
pretty scary, though...

Mobiles.Name: blacksmith nordic
Mobiles.Long_Description: The famous Nordic Blacksmith is here, telling some boring stories.
Mobiles.Description:
The famous Nordic Balcksmith says "I can sell you a sword for a reasonable 
price, just don't mess with my son."

Mobiles.Name: son
Mobiles.Long_Description: The Blacksmith's son is here, acting really annoyingly.
Mobiles.Description: You feel an urgent need to kill that little annoying bastard.

Mobiles.Name: daughter
Mobiles.Long_Description: The Blacksmith's daughter is here, knitting peacefully.
Mobiles.Description:
She looks a bit ugly, but very much relyable. She could never cheat her 
beloved ones.

Mobiles.Name: wife
Mobiles.Long_Description: The Blacksmith's wife is here, offering you a nice meal.
Mobiles.Description:
The Blacksmith's wife smiles peacefully, reminding you the old happy days 
hundreds of years ago, when she was a young beauty.

Mobiles.Name: villager fat
Mobiles.Long_Description: A fat villager is here, burping calmly.
Mobiles.Description: A fat villager seems to have a problem with tying his shoelaces.

Mobiles.Name: villager starving
Mobiles.Long_Description: A starving villager is here, begging for food for his family.
Mobiles.Description:
A starving villager has been robbed many times. He's too stupid to be alive 
anyway, so you know what you got to do.

Mobiles.Name: leiger disturbed hero
Mobiles.Long_Description: Leiger the disturbed hero, trying to find out what is going on.
Mobiles.Description: Leiger the disturbed hero says "Huh? What?" Go on, save him from his misery.

Mobiles.Name: villager musician
Mobiles.Long_Description: A village musician, playing his lyre in an especially annoying manner.
Mobiles.Description: A village musician is too occupied with his music to notice you.

Mobiles.Name: villager sneaky
Mobiles.Long_Description: A sneaky villager is here, standing too close to you.
Mobiles.Description: A sneaky villager moves closer and closer to you. You shouldn't trust him...

Mobiles.Name: villager thief
Mobiles.Long_Description: A village thief is here, trying to pick your pockets.
Mobiles.Description:
A village thief starts to whistle happily and looks as innocent as a 
newborn baby.

Mobiles.Name: suurtoll slowthinking
Mobiles.Long_Description: Suurtoll the slowthinking hero, having a dumb look on his face.
Mobiles.Description: Suurtoll the slowthinking hero says "Moh?"

Mobiles.Name: villager drinking
Mobiles.Long_Description: A beer drinking villager tries to look sober.
Mobiles.Description:
A beer drinking villager obviously wants to tell you something 
funny. "Hic" Unfortunately he's too drunk to make any sense.

Mobiles.Name: beauty arrogant
Mobiles.Long_Description: An arrogant village beauty, looking like she owns the place.
Mobiles.Description:
An arrogant village beauty says: "My boyfriends will punish you hard, if 
you keep staring at me."

Mobiles.Name: lady complaining
Mobiles.Long_Description: A complaining village lady, saying bad things to her husband.
Mobiles.Description:
A complaining village lady says: "Why do i always have to take out the 
garbage? Wanna know who is the real garbage....?"

Mobiles.Name: Lembitu
Mobiles.Long_Description: Lembitu is here, gathering the men to fight the evil crusaders.
Mobiles.Description:
Lembitu shouts: "Enemy has come to land! Stop drinking and come fight for 
your freedom!"

- My friends, my brothers,
  take the combat of today,
  that bloody, raging swordplay,
  as a pattern for the future.
  Men! stand like a wall of stone
  or like an iron bastion,
  like towers built of steel! -

Mobiles.Name: brother Olev
Mobiles.Long_Description: Olev the brother of Kalevipoeg is here, trying to look important.
Mobiles.Description: Olev the brother of Kalevipoeg says "Lets throw some rocks, heh?"

Mobiles.Name: brother Sulev
Mobiles.Long_Description: Sulev the brother of Kalevipoeg is here, trying to look important.
Mobiles.Description: Sulev the brother of Kalevipoeg says "You ain't gonna kill me now, are you?"

Mobiles.Name: brother Jalev
Mobiles.Long_Description: Jalev the brother of Kalevipoeg is here, trying to look important.
Mobiles.Description: Jalev the brother of Kalevipoeg says "I never liked my brother Kalevipoeg."

Mobiles.Name: brother Nolev
Mobiles.Long_Description: Nolev the brother of Kalevipoeg is here, trying to look important.
Mobiles.Description:
Nolev the brother of Kalevipoeg says "Actually I am the strongest in this 
country."

Mobiles.Name: brother Rulev
Mobiles.Long_Description: Rulev the brother of Kalevipoeg is here, trying to look important.
Mobiles.Description:
Rulev the brother of Kalevipoeg giggles and says "I feel like I'm only a 
prisoner in my manly body."

Mobiles.Name: spirit king Kalev
Mobiles.Short_Description: Spirit of the dead king Kalev
Mobiles.Long_Description: Spirit of the dead king Kalev is playing with his own skull.
Mobiles.Description:
Kalev answers under the sod, lift he's voice from beneath the earth, he 
speaks from his sepulcher: 

- I can't get up, young son,
  I can't wake up and rise!
  A boulder weighs on my body,
  a stone sets on my chest;
  globeflowers cover my brows,
  hepaticas grow on my eyes,
  red flowers bloom above my face.
  May the fair winds guide you,
  the gentle breezes counsel you
  and the stars in the skies give you
  WISDOM." -

Mobiles.Name: Linda wife weeping
Mobiles.Long_Description: Weeping Linda, wife of the dead king Kalev.
Mobiles.Description:
Linda cries like a baby. So many tears that you believe - there will be a
lake soon. You should give her a napkin.

- Ah! how wretched is this widow,
  this poor abandoned berry:
  like an unhored chamber
  or the walls of a roofless house;
  like a barren tract of land,
  staggered by every windstorm,
  reeled by the wet waves. -

Mobiles.Name: warrior ymera
Mobiles.Long_Description: An ymera warrior is hiding here in the bushes.
Mobiles.Description:
An ymera warrior is pretending to be brave.

- Don't cry, o maidens;
  don't be sad, my dears!
  We'll soon jail the thieves,
  we'll lock the robbers in irons. -

Mobiles.Name: evil crusader
Mobiles.Long_Description: An evil crusader is here, planning to rob the villages in Kalev's land.
Mobiles.Description:
An evil crusader has seen many battles... an ymera warrior wouldn't stand 
a chance against him... But they are tricky, they say "We came in peace!"

Mobiles.Name: traitor Kaupo
Mobiles.Long_Description: Kaupo the traitor is here, looking ashamed.
Mobiles.Description:
Kaupo the traitor's son has been kidnapped by crusaders... so he ain't got 
any options left but to obey the crusaders.

Mobiles.Name: rebane
Mobiles.Long_Description: A rebane runs around, chewing a bone.
Mobiles.Description:
A rebane looks like sneaky creature. You wonder if it isn't a human bone 
he is chewing.

Mobiles.Name: siil hedgehog
Mobiles.Long_Description: Siil the Hedgehog is teaching the heroes here.
Mobiles.Description: Siil the Hedgehog whispers: "Edgeways, edgeways o dear son of Kalev!"

Mobiles.Name: Lacplecis killer
Mobiles.Long_Description: Lacplecis the Bearkiller, looking like a wannabe.
Mobiles.Description:
Lacplacis doesn't seem much like a real hero. He's gonna be killed 
by bears pretty soon.

Mobiles.Name: bear
Mobiles.Long_Description: A cute bear runs from the hunters.
Mobiles.Description: A bear says: "Could you kill this wannabe hero Lacplecis please?"

Mobiles.Name: kurivaim
Mobiles.Long_Description: A kurivaim is guarding the passageway, looking naughty.
Mobiles.Description:
A kurivaim sticks his tongue out at you and rolls his eyes like a madman.

- Don't crow your happy day,
  boastfully, before the evening:
  the rooster that sings his praises at dawn
  might well be moaning by nightfall. -

Mobiles.Name: maiden kidnapped
Mobiles.Long_Description: A kidnapped maiden has been tied up here.
Mobiles.Description: A kidnapped maiden is weeping hopelessly.

Mobiles.Name: kalevipoeg
Mobiles.Long_Description: Kalevipoeg is here, fighting the Old Hornie.
Mobiles.Description: Now there is a really heroic hero. Too bad you have to kill him.

Mobiles.Name: old hornie
Mobiles.Long_Description: The Old Hornie is here, fighting Kalevipoeg.
Mobiles.Description:
The Old Hornie has long horns on his head and a wicked smile on his 
face. He seems like a nice guy and you wonder why Kalevipoeg is beating 
him up like that.

Objects.Name: aurora borealis
Objects.Description: Aurora Borealis - polar lights fallen from sky.

Extra_Descr_Data.Description: You look to bright light - you are blinded!

Objects.Name: wand black wooden
Objects.Description: A piece of dangerous-looking wood lies here.

Objects.Name: robe cotton
Objects.Description: A rough home-made robe lies on the ground.

Objects.Name: amulet
Objects.Description: A piece of stone with a leather cord, giving courage to it's owner.

Objects.Name: fingers human
Objects.Description: Some real human fingers, still bleeding, as you notice with discust.

Objects.Name: robe raindeerskin
Objects.Description: This garment looks very much weatherproof.

Objects.Name: hat winds
Objects.Short_Description: the hat of the four winds
Objects.Description:
Saams can hear the news from every corner of the world, when wearing this 
hat.

Objects.Name: amulet winds
Objects.Short_Description: the amulet of the four winds
Objects.Description: This stony amulet is used by wind worshippers.

Objects.Name: staff blue
Objects.Description: A piece of warm summer night has taken the form of a staff.

Objects.Name: dagger
Objects.Description: A recklessly made lethal weapon lies on the ground.

Objects.Name: cup beercup giant
Objects.Description: Hmm.. the cup looks like it could contain a whole barrel of a beer.

Objects.Name: sword cursed
Objects.Description: A sharp weapon lies here, possessed with evil.

Objects.Name: skirt cotton
Objects.Description: A simple long skirt. You won't look much attractive in it.

Objects.Name: vobla
Objects.Description: Ooohh, what joy, a dead fish, prefabricated with sun and salt. Yummy.

Objects.Name: spear wooden
Objects.Description: Obviously a pretty blunt weapon, yet deadly when used properly.

Objects.Name: shield wooden
Objects.Description: A piece of wood, covered with leather. It won't give you much protection.

Objects.Name: kannel
Objects.Description: An ancient music instrument, perfect for creating annoying sounds.

Objects.Name: spear
Objects.Description: A nice expensive-looking weapon.

Objects.Name: spear iron
Objects.Description:
You can almost hear the death cries of the innocent victims that lost their 
lives to that spear.

Objects.Name: club iron
Objects.Description: A simple, yet effective weapon. You got to be real strong to use it properly.

Objects.Name: shield iron
Objects.Description: A blood-stained and torn shield lies here abandoned.

Objects.Name: helmet iron
Objects.Description: A bucket-like helmet with small holes to look out of it.

Objects.Name: plate breastplate iron
Objects.Description: Some piece of a fine armor lies here.

Objects.Name: robe cross
Objects.Short_Description: a white robe with red cross
Objects.Description: A scary white robe with an evil-looking red cross drawn on it.

Objects.Name: amulet happy
Objects.Description: A simple sun-shaped amulet.

Objects.Name: skull
Objects.Description: A human skull like any other.

Objects.Name: cup beercup
Objects.Description: A wooden cup with an ornamented hang.

Objects.Name: bone human
Objects.Description: A nice bone, probably a rib .

Objects.Name: spear bearkilling
Objects.Description: This spear looks like a toy.

Objects.Name: pussnuga
Objects.Description: A weird ancient weapon, called pussnuga in some barbaric languages.

Objects.Name: plank
Objects.Description: A simple plank can be a very dangerous weapon in the right hands. Beware.

Objects.Name: horns giant
Objects.Description: Huge pale-green horns, torn off from the head of You Know Who.

Objects.Name: amulet evil
Objects.Description:
You see some miserable souls captured in there. Don't look too 
long, or you'll be the next.

Objects.Name: flowers globeflowers
Objects.Description: Beautiful flowers, smelling like the dead.

Objects.Name: drum
Objects.Description: A Drum is lying on the ground here, still buzzing evilly.

Objects.Name: vomit puddle
Objects.Description: Ewww... someone has been really sick here. No wonder.

Objects.Name: wheel spinning
Objects.Description: This instrument looks too complicated to make any sense.

Objects.Name: bridle
Objects.Description: A bridle lies here.

Objects.Name: plough
Objects.Description: A plough lies here.

Objects.Name: hoe
Objects.Description: A simple hoe lies here.

Objects.Name: harrow
Objects.Description: A nice harrow lies here.

Objects.Name: daisies
Objects.Description: Some daisies grow here.

Objects.Name: turnip
Objects.Description: A huge turnip grows here.

Objects.Name: corn-flower flower
Objects.Description: A sky-blue corn-flower grows here.

Objects.Name: nettle bush
Objects.Description: A bush of nettles grows here, looking for another victim. Ouch.

Objects.Name: bag corn
Objects.Description: A bag of full of golden corn lies  here.

Objects.Name: rat dead
Objects.Description: A dead rat lies here, covered with flies.

Objects.Name: mousetrap trap
Objects.Description: A mousetrap lies in the corner.

Objects.Name: pitchfork
Objects.Description: A wooden pitchfork has been stuck in the ground here.

Objects.Name: scythe
Objects.Description: A scythe hangs on the wall here.

Objects.Name: wooden spoon
Objects.Description: A huge wooden spoon, suitable for a person with enormous appetite.

Objects.Name: hat nailhat
Objects.Description: A hat made entirely of human nails, looking like it has some magical powers.

Objects.Name: corpse swallow
Objects.Description: Brutal villagers have murdered this innocent bird in cold blood. Revenge!

Objects.Name: strawshoes shoes
Objects.Description: Strange footwear made entirely out of straw.

Objects.Name: girdle
Objects.Description: A beautiful motley girdle, covered with happy ornament.

Objects.Name: figurine
Objects.Description: A roughly made figurine of some ancient northern god.

Objects.Name: brooch
Objects.Description: A silver brooch, beautiful in it's simplicity.

Objects.Name: key
Objects.Description: A shiny key to Tuuslar's Household.

Objects.Name: pile planks
Objects.Description:
A huge pile of planks lies here, too heavy to lift by any other than 
Kalevipoeg.

Objects.Name: axe
Objects.Description: A blunt axe hangs on the wall.

Rooms.Name: Gates to the Northern Tale
Rooms.Description:
Now the Northen Tale begins... Be brave, be careful...

- Wake, o grey and olden voices,
  send us secret kennings,
  tales of better times
  and the joys of dearer days.
  Come from Endla's waters
  o Vanemuine's daughter.
  You've stroked your silken hair
  at length in that silver mirror.
  Let us take truth's warrant,
  o ancient shadows;
  show the long-departed faces,
  show the coursing of the Kalev's,
  of the hardy men and witches.
  Let us sweep soaringly southward,
  take several steps toward the north,
  to the heather where my seedings
  flower in foreing fields. -

Rooms.Name: Stormy sea
Rooms.Description:
You are on the stormy sea. Salty water hurts your eyes, and you are nearly 
drowning under the enormous waves. You have also lost your sense of 
direction, and you feel like you wanna puke your guts out.

- Wave rolls after rolling wave,
  the wheeling billows
  swing against the stony shore,
  brust in foam against the beach.
  And the waves of our life,
  rolling in the chill of evening
  sway us toward our spelucher,
  beneath a blanket of sod. -

Rooms.Description:
You are on the stormy sea. Salty water hurts your eyes, and you are nearly

Rooms.Name: On the board of the old viking ship Lennuk
Rooms.Description:
You see traces of many hard battles on this ship. Shields with strange and 
evil ornaments lie on the boards, intimidating you.

Exits.Description: On the board of the old viking ship Lennuk

Rooms.Name: On the board of the old viking ship Lennuk
Rooms.Description:
You see traces of many hard battles on this ship. Shields with strange and 
evil ornaments lie on the boards, intimidating you.

Exits.Description: On the board of the old viking ship Lennuk

Rooms.Name: Captain room of Lennuk
Rooms.Description:
It's a nice cozy place with a compass and steering wheel. You notice some 
bottles of hard alcohol by the wheel.

Exits.Description: On the board of the old viking ship Lennuk

Rooms.Name: Northern coast
Rooms.Description:
Fierce waves roll to the rocky shore, trying to take you back to sea. Some 
stunted junipers grow here on the stones.

Rooms.Name: Northern coast
Rooms.Description:
Fierce waves roll to the rocky shore, trying to take you back to sea. Some 
stunted junipers grow here on the stones.

Rooms.Name: Northern coast
Rooms.Description:
Fierce waves roll to the rocky shore, trying to take you back to sea. Some 
stunted junipers grow here on the stones.

Rooms.Name: Northern coast
Rooms.Description:
Fierce waves roll to the rocky shore, trying to take you back to sea. Some 
stunted junipers grow here on the stones.

Rooms.Name: Door to Tuuslar's household
Rooms.Description:
Through the junipers you see a large conical building, obviously made of 
animal skins and wood. The skin-made conic is enshrouded with gray and 
stinky smoke, it feels like somebody is being burned alive in there.

Rooms.Name: The First floor of the Tuuslar's Household
Rooms.Description:
The smell of many unwashed bodies and clothing used for months makes you 
sick. Smoke gets even thicker inside. You hear loud voices speaking in an 
ancient and barbaric language, and noises of struggle.

Rooms.Name: The First floor of the Tuuslar's Household
Rooms.Description:
The smell of many unwashed bodys and clothing used for months makes you 
sick. Smoke gets even thicker inside. You hear loud voices speaking in an 
ancient and barbaric language, and noises of struggle.

Exits.Description: The First floor of the Tuuslar's Household
The Second floor of the Tuuslar's Household

Rooms.Name: The Second floor of the Tuuslar's Household
Rooms.Description:
You see traces of a barbaric feast. There are a lot of bones on the floor, 
some chewed and some covered with bloody flesh. A huge barrel sits in the 
corner, surrounded with a puddle of some smelly liquid.
Simple chairs and a long table are covered with dirt.

Exits.Description: The Second floor of the Tuuslar's Household
The First floor of the Tuuslar's Household

Rooms.Name: The Second floor of the Tuuslar's Household
Rooms.Description:
You see traces of a barbaric feast. There are a lot of bones on the floor,

Simple chairs and a long table are covered with dirt.

Exits.Description: The Second floor of the Tuuslar's Household
The Second floor of the Tuuslar's Household

Simple chairs and a long table are covered with dirt.

Exits.Description: The Second floor of the Tuuslar's Household
The Third floor of the Tuuslar's Household

Rooms.Name: The Third floor of the Tuuslar's Household
Rooms.Description:
You are standing in an empty room with two simple wooden doors. From the 
south you can hear an annoyingly scolding voice, and some merry singing 
from the north.

Exits.Description: The Second floor of the Tuuslar's Household

Rooms.Name: Tuuslar's bedroom
Rooms.Description:
You can smell a strange perfume, possibly made of human blood and some 
other unusual components. Smelly old animal-skins lie in the corner, and 
some linen clothes are scattered all over the place.

Exits.Description: The Third floor of the Tuuslar's Household

Rooms.Name: Tuuslar's study
Rooms.Description:
A simple wooden desk is here with a wooden chair. Along the walls lie bags 
with all kinds of strange herbs. On the walls you notice some pictures of 
evil faces, and some paintings of slaughtering innocent creatures.

Rooms.Name: Sauna
Rooms.Description:
You stand in hot steam, wondering if it isn't a torturing chamber. A wooden 
bench is here, and in the corner you see a strange fireplace without a flue.
A small stairway leads you down to a refreshing pool of cold water.

Rooms.Name: Sauna pool
Rooms.Description:
You dive into the cool dark water. When you stick your head out of the pool 
again, you see that everything has changed. Sauna is gone for good. You see 
small campfires all around you, and you can hear a lot of strange singing.

Rooms.Name: Northland
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on soft lichen. These plains are empty as far as you can 
see, only some stunted birches grow here.

Rooms.Name: Northland
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on soft lichen. These plains are empty as far as you can 
see, only some stunted birches grow here.

Rooms.Name: Northland
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on soft lichen. These plains are empty as far as you can 
see, only some stunted birches grow here.

Rooms.Name: Northland
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on soft lichen. These plains are empty as far as you can

Rooms.Name: Thule
Rooms.Description:
Under the bloodred sky you walk. Sun never sets here, nor rises. The cold 
northern plains of snow and ice make you feel like you are the only living 
creature on the whole earth. You realize that there is no escape from here. 
Once you step over the edge of the world, you will remain a prisoner till 
the end of you days.

Rooms.Name: Island of the famous Nordic Blacksmith
Rooms.Description:
There's a cozy-looking cottage right on the shore of the island. You see 
all kinds of swords, daggers, axes and other fine weapons standing in the 
straight rows in front of the building.

Rooms.Name: Blacksmith's Cottage
Rooms.Description:
You stand in a fair commodious building with wide windows. There's a small 
fireplace in the center of the room, and you feel the aroma of a delicious 
fresh hotpot.

Exits.Description: Island of the Famous Nordic Blacksmith

Rooms.Name: South coast
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on a sandy seaside. Fresh wind blows calmly through your 
hair. You can hear faint sounds of a village from the south.

Rooms.Name: South coast
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on a sandy seaside. Fresh wind blows calmly through your 
hair. You can hear faint sounds of a village from the south.

Rooms.Name: Forest
Rooms.Description:
Huge oaktrees grow here, you can see the squirrels and little birds having 
a peep at you from their homes in the tops of the trees.

Rooms.Name: Forest
Rooms.Description:
Huge oaktrees grow here, you can see the squirrels and little birds having 
a peep at you from their homes in the tops of the trees.

Huge oaktrees grow here, you can see the squirrels and little birds having 
a peep at you from their homes in the tops of the trees.

Rooms.Name: Kalev's dooryard
Rooms.Description:
Buildings surround the yard bearing witness to a wealthy farm. Near pasture 
stands a paddlock shaded by a fine oaktree.

Rooms.Name: Kalev's realms
Rooms.Description:
Obviously the dwellers of this land are rather farmers than fighters. You 
see huge greenhouses and pretty golden fields of corn. Hundreds of appletrees 
are full of mellow fruits.

Rooms.Name: Tomb of old king Kalev
Rooms.Description:
Kalvev's tomb is basically a pile of grey moss-grown stones, gathered here 
as a mortuary in an ancient northern manner.

- Linda, weeping widow,
  then started to carry stones
  for a cairn on Kalev's grave.
  She wanted to set a landmark
  for the sons of later generations;
  for future daughters
  to see where Kalev's tomb lay,
  the pallet of the graveyard. -

Rooms.Name: Kalev's Happy House
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on the first floor of Kalev's House. The house is nicely 
taken care of, everything points out the regardful touch of the Lady of the 
House. Even the wooden furniture is perfectly clean.

Rooms.Description:
The second floor of the Kalev's house just the opposite to the first. 
Scattered clothes, armorpieces and weapons indicate to young and reckless 
dwellers.

Rooms.Name: Koljala village
Rooms.Description:
Well-built wooden houses lie in straight rows here. Hard-working villagers 
seem to be happy and rich.

Rooms.Name: Valjala village
Rooms.Description:
You see a couple of luxurious manors surrounded by dozens of pathetic huts. 
A few well-fed villagers walk around proudly, paying no attention to their 
poor and miserable neighbors.

Rooms.Name: Mustjala village
Rooms.Description:
Some little cottages with thatched roofs are scattered here. You see some 
villagers here gathered around the campfire.

Exits.Description: On the base of Bear Hill

Rooms.Name: Ymera battleground
Rooms.Description:
Thick bushes and some small hills make this place perfect for ambushing and 
hiding. You can feel the presence of somebody, but you don't see anything.

- A steep, still vale of death,
  the bloodthristy battlefield,
  gathers bodies by thousands
  to rest in the embrance of dust,
  to sleep in the lawn's lap. -

Rooms.Name: Ymera battleground
Rooms.Description:
Some dangerous-looking figures with iron clothes and loud voices have 
gathered here around the campfire. You hear a lot of arrogant laughing and 
bragging.

Rooms.Name: On the base of Bear Hill
Rooms.Description:
You are standing on the base of Bear Hill, with your feet stuck in the 
dense undergrowth. You hear distant noises of a struggle from above.

Rooms.Name: Bear Hill
Rooms.Description:
The view is magnificent from here. You can even see the hostile lands far 
away in the south. Here lies the southern borderline of the Kalev's realms.

Exits.Description: On the base of Bear Hill

Rooms.Name: Dark forest
Rooms.Description:
You can see no movement in these woods, neither hear any sound. No bird 
sings, no animal runs along. Ancient gray trees are all you can see here, 
and you get a feeling that they can see you too.

Rooms.Name: Dark forest
Rooms.Description:
You can see no movement in these woods, neither hear any sound. No bird 
sings, no animal runs along. Ancient gray trees are all you can see here, 
and you get a feeling that they can see you too.

You can feel the chilling freeze glooming out from between some deep black 
rocks. It appears to come from the entrance to some passageway leading you 
down to darkness.

Rooms.Name: Passage
Rooms.Description:
Air is still here, but yet you can feel some movement around you. There are 
flaming torches on the walls, giving just enough light for you to apprehend 
the darkness.

the darkness.

Rooms.Name: Dark passage
Rooms.Description:
Benumbing fear sneaks around feet, as you hear the soft weeping coming from 
below. Torches have burned out, you have to fumble for your way down.

Rooms.Name: Dark underground
Rooms.Description:
Deep red light glows from below, through the stony floor. Some tortured 
figures lie on the cold stone floor in the corners here, weeping hopelessly.

Rooms.Name: Darkest underground
Rooms.Description:
You seem to stand on the thin air. There is nothing more but the red light, 
no floor nor ceiling, just the light all around you, driving you insane.

Rooms.Name: Old Hornie's lair
Rooms.Description:
You are in a small dimly lit room, covered in dust. A huge ancient armchair,
 ornamented with human skulls, standing in the center of the room, leaves 
you no other choice but to think that you have entered the throne hall of 
the Old Hornie himself.

Rooms.Name: Vanemuine the song-wizard's room
Rooms.Description:
Tales gathered and written by F.R. Kreutzwald

- Vanemuine, lend me your lyre.
  A sweet song is stirring my senses
  and I long unfold in song
  the legacy of ancient ages. -

All lyrics translated by George Kurman
English Translation copyright UNESCO 1982
